Dashboard Screen

After successfully signing in, the application displays the dashboard - the default landing page of the application. The app displays the summary of the information relevant to the logged in admin user. The features available to you in the app depends on your role and permissions associated with the role.

In the current app version, the dashboard displays the following standard widget for all users.

  • Messages (My Queue and New Messages)

Click here to view the various icons used on the dashboard and their description
IconDescription

ATM

Online Banking

Mobile Banking

Messages (My Queue and New Messages)

My Queue displays the total number of messages assigned to the logged in admin user. The count includes number of new and in progress messages. Click View All to view all the messages available under My Queue tab in the Messages module. New messages displays the total number of new messages received by the bank or credit union. It also displays the top four message categories with the maximum number of new messages for which the action has not been taken. Click View all to get the complete list of messages available in the New tab in Messages module.

Supported Languages and Formats

You can change the language from your browser settings and re-login into the Spotlight application after you change the language.

The application supports five European languages - UK English, German, Spanish, and French. The default selected language is US English. When you select any language, the application automatically changes the language, currency format, date format, and  number format to match with the geographical location of the selected language. 

Here is the list of languages and their corresponding formats:
